verses.text: My son , forget not my law ; but let thine heart keep my commandments :
For length of days , and long life , and peace , shall they add to thee.\f + \fr 3.2 \ft long…: Heb. years of life\f*
Let not mercy and truth forsake thee: bind them about thy neck ; write them upon the table of thine heart :
So shalt thou find favour and good understanding in the sight of God and man.\f + \fr 3.4 \ft good…: or, good success\f* \p
¶ Trust in the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* with all thine heart ; and lean not unto thine own understanding.
In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths. \p
¶ Be not wise in thine own eyes : fear the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and depart from evil.
It shall be health to thy navel , and marrow to thy bones.\f + \fr 3.8 \ft health: Heb. medicine\f*\f + \fr 3.8 \ft marrow: Heb. watering, or, moistening\f*
Honour the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* with thy substance , and with the firstfruits of all thine increase :
So shall thy barns be filled with plenty , and thy presses shall burst out with new wine. \p
¶ My son , despise not the chastening of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*; neither be weary of his correction :
For whom the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* loveth he correcteth ; even as a father the son \add in whom\add* he delighteth. \p
¶ Happy \add is\add* the man \add that\add* findeth wisdom , and the man \add that\add* getteth understanding.\f + \fr 3.13 \ft that getteth…: Heb. that draweth out understanding\f*
For the merchandise of it \add is\add* better than the merchandise of silver , and the gain thereof than fine gold.
She \add is\add* more precious than rubies : and all the things thou canst desire are not to be compared unto her.
Length of days \add is\add* in her right hand ; \add and\add* in her left hand riches and honour.
Her ways \add are\add* ways of pleasantness , and all her paths \add are\add* peace.
She \add is\add* a tree of life to them that lay hold upon her: and happy \add is every one\add* that retaineth her.
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* by wisdom hath founded the earth ; by understanding hath he established the heavens.\f + \fr 3.19 \ft established: or, prepared\f*
By his knowledge the depths are broken up , and the clouds drop down the dew. \p
¶ My son , let not them depart from thine eyes : keep sound wisdom and discretion :
So shall they be life unto thy soul , and grace to thy neck.
Then shalt thou walk in thy way safely , and thy foot shall not stumble.
When thou liest down , thou shalt not be afraid : yea, thou shalt lie down , and thy sleep shall be sweet.
Be not afraid of sudden fear , neither of the desolation of the wicked , when it cometh.
For the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* shall be thy confidence , and shall keep thy foot from being taken. \p
¶ Withhold not good from them to whom it is due , when it is in the power of thine hand to do \add it\add*.\f + \fr 3.27 \ft them…: Heb. the owners thereof\f*
Say not unto thy neighbour , Go , and come again , and to morrow I will give ; when thou hast it by thee.
Devise not evil against thy neighbour , seeing he dwelleth securely by thee.\f + \fr 3.29 \ft Devise…: or, Practise no evil\f* \p
¶ Strive not with a man without cause , if he have done thee no harm. \p
¶ Envy thou not the oppressor , and choose none of his ways.\f + \fr 3.31 \ft the oppressor: Heb. a man of violence\f*
For the froward \add is\add* abomination to the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: but his secret \add is\add* with the righteous. \p
¶ The curse of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add is\add* in the house of the wicked : but he blesseth the habitation of the just.
Surely he scorneth the scorners : but he giveth grace unto the lowly.
The wise shall inherit glory : but shame shall be the promotion of fools.\f + \fr 3.35 \ft shall be…: Heb. exalteth the fools\f*
